          "order": 1,
          "title": "ALIGNING TEXT-TO-IMAGE MODELS USING HUMAN FEEDBACK",
          "summary": "In this work we see additional evidence that alignment improves capabilities. Previous research seems to have mostly been focused on capabilities that are weakly aligned to human preference (e.g., improving FID or SOTA on a benchmark). Now, however, we find that if we train a reward model on human feedback data, our models become significantly more useful. They outline a “reward weighted likelihood maximization” scheme. Their experiments are constrained to categories of count, color, and background.",
          "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2302.12192?utm_source=tldrai",
          "reading_time_minutes": 34,
          "source_domain": "arxiv.org",
          "content_type": "editorial",
          "is_sponsor": false
        },
